The paper presents a method that combines a pre-trained Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) with a Reinforcement Learning (RL) agent as a Question Answering (QA) model to improve the accuracy and efficiency of a visual symptom checker for skin conditions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses RL to optimize the QA system, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of RL also involves training a Deep Q-Network (DQN), which is a type of neural network, and this falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of the QA system in a medical context, which involves human-computer interaction, and this falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to guide the QA system, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
